TWA
EMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE
INTERNATIONAL ADVANCE SCHEDULES
ISSUED DATE JANUARY 31, 1975
TRANSMITTAL 4-75
EFFECTIVE APRIL 1, 1975
(Except as Noted)
TWA's Peak Summer schedule program includes 170 weekly transatlantic roundtrips, of which 84
will be operated with Boeing 747s. These are:
• Twice daily New York-London
Daily Chicago-London
• Daily San Francisco/Los Angeles-London/Paris
• Daily Boston-London
• Daily New York-Paris
• Daily New York-Frankfurt
• Daily New York-Lisbon/Madrid
• Daily New York-Madrid
Daily New York-Milan
• Daily New York-Rome
• Daily New York-Athens-Tel Aviv
ISED
Additional improvements in this schedule include:
• New York-Shannon - increase to twice daily nonstop service.
• New York-Cairo - increase to daily two-stop service.
• Madrid-Rome/Athens - increase to daily service.
• Washington-Paris - reinstatement of daily nonstop service.
• New York-Switzerland - daily nonstop service to Zurich and Geneva.
• New York-Paris - increase to twice daily nonstop service.
The following additional U.S. cities will receive direct daily service to Europe:
San Francisco, Oakland, Las Vegas, Tucson, Phoenix, Denver, Kansas City,
St. Louis, Detroit, Cleveland, Pittsburgh, and Philadelphia.
